HEADWORD: Scouse
<hw>Scouse</hw> <pr>(skous)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A sailor's dish. Bread <ex>scouse</ex> contains no meat;
lob<ex>scouse</ex> contains meat, etc. See <er>Lobscouse</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Ham. Nav. Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

